THE GREAT WALL OF CHINA
DONG KINGMAN

THE GREAT WALL OF CHINA
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
In the mountains north of Peking (Beijing), looking toward Inner Mongolia, is the Great Wall.The lergest
man-made structure on earth, the 3,000 mile wall was begun in the third century B.C. It took over
200 years to complete. The Peking area also offers such wondrous sights as the Ming Tombs, the
Forbidden City, the Great Hall, Chairman Mao's Memorial and the Temple of Heaven. Shanghai,
Soochow (Suzhou), Hangchow (Hangzhou), and Canton (Guangzhou), among many other cities,
offer equally breathtaking vistas
A visit to the People's Republic of China is a unique and totally remarkable experience; now only
14 hours away on Pan Am's 74/SP Clippers
